the princess's interview!

245
00:31:14,705 --> 00:31:17,606
Eleven forty-five!

246
00:31:17,810 --> 00:31:19,437
Oh, sh!

247
00:32:03,578 --> 00:32:04,875
Hi, Joe.

248
00:32:05,080 --> 00:32:07,743
- Morning, Joe.
- Hello, honey.

249
00:32:11,457 --> 00:32:15,053
Mr Hennessy has been
looking for you.

250
00:32:15,262 --> 00:32:16,786
Uh-oh.

251
00:32:18,835 --> 00:32:20,131
Thanks a lot, hon.

252
00:32:22,270 --> 00:32:23,793
Come in.

253
00:32:30,975 --> 00:32:33,635
- Looking for me?
- Just coming to work?

254
00:32:33,844 --> 00:32:37,572
- Who, me?
- We start at 8.30 in this office.

255
00:32:37,780 --> 00:32:41,270
- We pick up our assignments...
- l got mine last night.

256
00:32:41,482 --> 00:32:44,574
- What assignment was that?
- The princess, 1 1 .45.

257
00:32:47,786 --> 00:32:50,344
You've already been to the interview?

258
00:32:50,556 --> 00:32:52,079
Sure, l just got back.

259
00:32:53,690 --> 00:32:57,418
- Well, well. All my apologies.
- lt's all right.

260
00:32:57,627 --> 00:32:59,490
- lnteresting.
- No, just routine.

261
00:32:59,694 --> 00:33:01,991
Did she answer
all the questions on the list?

262
00:33:02,197 --> 00:33:05,857
Of course. l've got 'em
right here somewhere.

263
00:33:06,065 --> 00:33:09,089
Don't disturb yourself,
l have a copy here.

264
00:33:09,301 --> 00:33:13,758
How did Her Highness react to
the idea of a European Federation?

265
00:33:13,971 --> 00:33:17,837
- She thought it was just fine.
- She did?

266
00:33:19,208 --> 00:33:23,266
- She thought there'd be two effects.
- Two?

267
00:33:23,478 --> 00:33:27,844
- The direct and the indirect.
- Remarkable.

268
00:33:28,047 --> 00:33:33,607
Naturally, she thought that the indirect
would not be as direct as the direct.

269
00:33:34,784 --> 00:33:37,012
- That is, not right away.
- No.

270
00:33:37,220 --> 00:33:40,312
Later on, of course, nobody knows.

271
00:33:41,522 --> 00:33:43,613
Well, well.

272
00:33:43,824 --> 00:33:45,949
That was a shrewd observation.

273
00:33:46,593 --> 00:33:51,584
They fool you, these royal kids.
They're smarter than we suspect.

274
00:33:51,796 --> 00:33:57,459
How did she feel about
the future friendship of nations?

275
00:33:57,666 --> 00:34:02,726
Youth. She felt that
the youth of the world

276
00:34:02,937 --> 00:34:07,065
must lead the way to a better world.

277
00:34:08,407 --> 00:34:09,895
Original.

278
00:34:11,076 --> 00:34:14,043
By the way, what was she wearing?

279
00:34:15,345 --> 00:34:19,939
- You mean what did she have on?
- That's usually what it means.

280
00:34:20,149 --> 00:34:23,479
- ls it too warm for you?
- No, l just hurried over here.

281
00:34:23,683 --> 00:34:26,310
Naturally, with a story
of these dimensions.

282
00:34:26,519 --> 00:34:30,146
- Did you say she was wearing grey?
- No, l didn't.

283
00:34:30,355 --> 00:34:35,346
- She usually wears grey.
- Well, it was a kind of a grey.

284
00:34:35,558 --> 00:34:38,491
l think l know the dress,
it has a gold collar...

285
00:34:38,694 --> 00:34:42,024
That's the one. l didn't know
exactly how to describe it.

286
00:34:42,229 --> 00:34:45,957
l think you described it very well,

287
00:34:46,166 --> 00:34:50,328
in view of the fact that
she was taken violently ill at 3 a.m.,

288
00:34:50,535 --> 00:34:52,524
put to bed with a high fever,

289
00:34:52,736 --> 00:34:57,637
and has had all her appointments
for today cancelled in toto!

290
00:34:57,840 --> 00:35:03,071
- ln toto?
- Yes, Mr Bradley, in toto.

291
00:35:05,878 --> 00:35:10,779
- That's pretty hard to swallow.
- ln view of the fact you just left her.

292
00:35:10,981 --> 00:35:14,971
Here it is, Mr Bradley, all over the
front page of every paper in Rome.

293
00:35:15,185 --> 00:35:18,118
All right, l overslept.
lt can happen to anybody.

294
00:35:18,320 --> 00:35:20,650
lf you ever got up
and read a morning paper,

295
00:35:20,855 --> 00:35:24,948
you might discover little news events,
little items of general interest,

296
00:35:25,158 --> 00:35:28,956
that might stop you getting
immersed in such a gold-plated,

297
00:35:29,161 --> 00:35:32,754
triple-decked, star-spangled
lie as you have just told me.

298
00:35:32,963 --> 00:35:36,556
lf l were you l'd try some other
business, like mattress testing!

299
00:35:36,766 --> 00:35:40,131
- ls this the princess?
- Yes, Mr Bradley.

300
00:35:40,335 --> 00:35:44,292
lt isn't Annie Oakley, Dorothy Lamour
or Madame Chiang Kai-Shek.

301
00:35:44,504 --> 00:35:47,869
Take a good look. You might
interview her again some day.

302
00:35:48,072 --> 00:35:50,436
Am l fired?

303
00:35:50,641 --> 00:35:55,007
No. When l want to fire you,
you won't have to ask.

304
00:35:55,212 --> 00:35:56,735
You'll know you're fired.

305
00:36:00,781 --> 00:36:02,077
The man's mad.

306
00:36:25,465 --> 00:36:27,988
Giovanni, it's Joe Bradley.

307
00:36:28,199 --> 00:36:29,790
Now listen carefully.

308
00:36:30,001 --> 00:36:34,662
Hurry up to my place and see
if there's somebody there, asleep.

309
00:36:35,238 --> 00:36:38,535
Aha. Si, Mr Joe.

310
00:36:38,740 --> 00:36:42,070
l look, you wait.

311
00:37:02,823 --> 00:37:05,984
- Mr Joe?
- Yeah. Tell me.

312
00:37:10,094 --> 00:37:12,890
Giovanni, l love you! Now listen.

313
00:37:13,096 --> 00:37:15,119
Yes, Mr Joe.

314
00:37:16,832 --> 00:37:19,355
A gun? No.

315
00:37:19,568 --> 00:37:22,501
Yes, a gun, a knife, anything.

316
00:37:22,702 --> 00:37:26,659
But nobody goes in
and nobody goes out.

317
00:37:27,639 --> 00:37:29,230
OK.

318
00:37:41,848 --> 00:37:44,314
You still here?

319
00:37:44,516 --> 00:37:46,813
What would a real interview
with this dame be worth?

320
00:37:47,019 --> 00:37:51,249
- Are you referring to Her Highness?
- l'm not referring to Annie Oakley...

321
00:37:51,454 --> 00:37:53,113
- How much?
- What do you care?

322
00:37:53,323 --> 00:37:56,620
- You've got no chance...
- lf l did, how much?

323
00:37:56,824 --> 00:38:01,588
Just a plain talk on world
conditions might be worth 250.

324
00:38:01,795 --> 00:38:04,261
Her views on clothes, a lot more.

325
00:38:04,463 --> 00:38:05,951
- Maybe 1 ,000.
- Dollars?

326
00:38:06,164 --> 00:38:10,257
l'm talking about
her views on everything.

327
00:38:10,467 --> 00:38:14,833
The private and secret
longings of a princess.

328
00:38:15,037 --> 00:38:18,664
Her innermost thoughts, as revealed
to your own correspondent,

329
00:38:18,873 --> 00:38:25,708
in a private, personal,
exclusive interview.

330
00:38:30,914 --> 00:38:35,314
Can't use it, huh?
l didn't think you'd like it.

331
00:38:38,218 --> 00:38:39,514
Come here.

332
00:38:41,755 --> 00:38:45,280
- Love angle too, l suppose?
- Practically all love angle.

333
00:38:45,490 --> 00:38:47,217
With pictures?

334
00:38:47,426 --> 00:38:48,949
Could be. How much?

335
00:38:49,160 --> 00:38:53,218
That particular story would be worth
five grand to any news service.

336
00:38:53,429 --> 00:38:56,260
But tell me, Mr Bradley,
if you are sober,

337
00:38:56,464 --> 00:38:59,522
how you are going to
obtain this fantastic interview.

338
00:38:59,733 --> 00:39:03,132
l'll enter her sick room
disguised as a thermometer.

339
00:39:03,337 --> 00:39:07,703
You said five grand?
l want you to shake on that.

340
00:39:09,341 --> 00:39:12,968
You realise she's in bed
and leaves for Athens tomorrow?

341
00:39:13,176 --> 00:39:16,473
- Yes.
- l'd like to make a little side bet.

342
00:39:16,677 --> 00:39:20,634
Five hundred says
you don't come up with the story.

343
00:39:26,985 --> 00:39:31,477
- What are you looking at that for?
- Just want to see what day it is.

344
00:39:32,422 --> 00:39:36,584
- lt's a deal.
- Now l'd like you to shake.

345
00:39:39,560 --> 00:39:42,152
You're into me for about $500 now.

346
00:39:42,362 --> 00:39:45,420
When you lose this bet,
you'll owe me $1 ,000.

347
00:39:45,631 --> 00:39:48,120
You poor sucker,
l'll practically own you.

348
00:39:48,332 --> 00:39:52,164
You practically have for a couple
of years but that's all over.

349
00:39:52,369 --> 00:39:57,167
l'm going to win that money and buy
a one-way ticket back to New York.

350
00:39:57,372 --> 00:39:59,770
Go on, l love to hear you whine.

351
00:39:59,973 --> 00:40:03,065
When l'm back in a real
newsroom, l'll think of you,

352
00:40:03,275 --> 00:40:07,675
sitting here with an empty leash
and nobody to twitch for you.

353
00:40:07,879 --> 00:40:11,040
So long, pigeon.

354
00:40:39,600 --> 00:40:42,089
- Signor Bradley.
- Everything OK, Giovanni?

355
00:40:42,301 --> 00:40:46,497
Si Signor Joe.
Nobody come, nobody go.

356
00:40:46,705 --> 00:40:50,104
- Absolutely nobody.
- Swell, thanks a lot.

357
00:40:52,108 --> 00:40:58,669
Oh... Giovanni...
How'd you like to make some money?

358
00:40:58,879 --> 00:41:00,436
- Money?
- Yeah.

359
00:41:00,647 --> 00:41:04,012
That's the stuff. l've got a sure thing.

360
00:41:04,216 --> 00:41:08,173
- Double your money back in two days.
- Double my money?

361
00:41:08,385 --> 00:41:11,875
l need a little investment
capital to swing the deal.

362
00:41:12,088 --> 00:41:14,987
Now if you'll lend me a little cash...

363
00:41:17,825 --> 00:41:22,987
You owe me two months rent

364
00:41:23,195 --> 00:41:26,560
and you want me to lend you money?

365
00:41:26,864 --> 00:41:29,422
No.

366
00:41:30,767 --> 00:41:33,064
Tomorrow you'll be sorry.

367
00:42:38,611 --> 00:42:39,907
Your Highness...?

368
00:42:42,048 --> 00:42:44,913
Your Royal Highness...?

369
00:42:48,152 --> 00:42:49,617
Yes, what is it?

370
00:44:29,752 --> 00:44:33,550
Dear Dr Bannochhoven...

371
00:44:34,789 --> 00:44:37,221
Oh, sure, yes, well...

372
00:44:37,424 --> 00:44:41,517
You're fine, much better.
ls there anything you want?

373
00:44:41,726 --> 00:44:46,024
- So many things.
- Yes? Well, tell the doctor.

374
00:44:46,230 --> 00:44:48,287
Tell the good doctor everything.

375
00:44:49,365 --> 00:44:52,298
l dreamt and l dreamt...

376
00:44:52,501 --> 00:44:56,026
Yes? Well, what did you dream?

377
00:44:57,871 --> 00:45:01,168
l dreamt l was asleep in the street,

378
00:45:01,373 --> 00:45:07,832
and a young man came,
he was tall and strong.

379
00:45:08,045 --> 00:45:10,876
He was so mean to me.

380
00:45:11,913 --> 00:45:14,072
He was?

381
00:45:19,919 --> 00:45:22,546
lt was wonderful.

382
00:45:55,042 --> 00:45:56,735
Good morning.

383
00:46:00,845 --> 00:46:06,041
- Where's Dr Bannochhoven?
- l'm afraid l don't know him.

384
00:46:06,250 --> 00:46:09,910
- Wasn't l talking to him just now?
- Afraid not.

385
00:46:12,520 --> 00:46:14,645
Have l had an accident?

386
00:46:15,623 --> 00:46:17,748
No.

387
00:46:18,757 --> 00:46:22,087
Quite safe for me to sit up, huh?

388
00:46:22,694 --> 00:46:24,489
Perfectly.

389
00:46:34,636 --> 00:46:36,159
Thank you.

390
00:46:45,843 --> 00:46:47,832
Are these yours?

391
00:46:54,581 --> 00:46:59,242
- Did you lose something?
- No.

392
00:47:01,953 --> 00:47:06,319
Would you be so kind
as to tell me where l am?

393
00:47:07,057 --> 00:47:10,684
This is what is laughingly
known as my apartment.

394
00:47:10,892 --> 00:47:16,828
- Did you bring me here by force?
- No, no. Quite the contrary.

395
00:47:18,163 --> 00:47:24,121
- Have l been here all night...alone?
- lf you don't count me, yes.

396
00:47:27,069 --> 00:47:30,127
So l've spent the night here with you?

397
00:47:30,873 --> 00:47:35,864
Well, l don't know that
l'd use those words exactly,

398
00:47:36,075 --> 00:47:42,374
but from a certain angle, yes.

399
00:47:57,990 --> 00:48:00,752
- How do you do?
- How do you do?

400
00:48:00,959 --> 00:48:04,222
- And you are?
- Bradley, Joe Bradley.

401
00:48:04,428 --> 00:48:08,260
- Delighted.
- You don't know how delighted l am.

402
00:48:08,464 --> 00:48:11,989
- You may sit down.
- Thank you very much.

403
00:48:17,469 --> 00:48:19,436
What's your name?

404
00:48:22,840 --> 00:48:28,105
- You may call me Anya.
- Well thank you, Anya.

405
00:48:31,279 --> 00:48:33,302
- Coffee?
- What time is it?

406
00:48:33,513 --> 00:48:35,001
About one-thirty.

407
00:48:35,215 --> 00:48:37,738
One-thirty! l must get dressed and go!

408
00:48:37,950 --> 00:48:40,781
Why the hurry? There's lots of time.

409
00:48:40,986 --> 00:48:44,545
No there isn't, and l've been
enough trouble as it is.

410
00:48:44,754 --> 00:48:48,711
Trouble?
You're not what l'd call trouble.

411
00:48:50,725 --> 00:48:55,023
- l'm not?
- l'll run a bath for you.

412
00:49:12,706 --> 00:49:14,569
There you are.

413
00:49:56,503 --> 00:49:58,230
Here we go now.

414
00:50:00,638 --> 00:50:04,662
There you are, that does it. All right.

415
00:50:04,875 --> 00:50:07,535
Give me a little slack, will you?

416
00:50:09,677 --> 00:50:11,506
lrving! Why don't you answer?

417
00:50:11,712 --> 00:50:14,941
lt's Joe. Can you
get here in five minutes?

418
00:50:15,149 --> 00:50:18,378
No, l can't come now, Joe, l'm busy.

419
00:50:18,583 --> 00:50:20,811
Oh, no.

420
00:50:21,018 --> 00:50:24,746
Joe, l'm up to my ears in work.

421
00:50:24,954 --> 00:50:28,444
Get into your next outfit.
What kind of a scoop, Joe?

422
00:50:28,657 --> 00:50:31,123
l can't talk over the phone.

423
00:50:31,325 --> 00:50:33,723
This whole thing
might easily blow sky-high.

424
00:50:33,927 --> 00:50:36,416
lt's front-page stuff,
that's all l can say.

425
00:50:36,629 --> 00:50:39,619
lt might be political or
a scandal, l don't know,

426
00:50:39,831 --> 00:50:42,389
but it's a big story.
l need pictures.

427
00:50:42,599 --> 00:50:46,192
But l can't come now, Joe, l'm busy.

428
00:50:46,401 --> 00:50:49,800
And l'm meeting Francesca
at Rocca's in half an hour.

429
00:51:48,944 --> 00:51:52,139
- Don't understand.
- Don't understand?

430
00:52:13,060 --> 00:52:14,686
There you are.

431
00:52:15,560 --> 00:52:20,893
l was looking at all the people.
lt must be fun to live in a place like this.

432
00:52:21,098 --> 00:52:25,122
lt has its moments. l can give you
a commentary on each apartment.

433
00:52:25,335 --> 00:52:27,198
l must go.

434
00:52:27,970 --> 00:52:34,702
- l only waited to say goodbye.
- Goodbye? But we've only just met!

435
00:52:35,007 --> 00:52:37,405
- How about breakfast?
- l haven't time.

436
00:52:38,043 --> 00:52:42,500
lt must be a pretty important date
to run off without eating.

437
00:52:42,713 --> 00:52:46,169
- lt is.
- l'll go with you.

438
00:52:46,381 --> 00:52:49,075
That's all right, l can find the place.

439
00:52:51,552 --> 00:52:54,713
Thank you for letting me
sleep in your bed.

440
00:52:55,622 --> 00:53:00,750
- That's all right. Think nothing of it.
- lt was very considerate of you.

441
00:53:00,958 --> 00:53:03,720
You must've been awfully
uncomfortable on that couch.

442
00:53:03,927 --> 00:53:06,519
No, l do it all the time.

443
00:53:11,131 --> 00:53:14,360
- Goodbye, Mr Bradley.
- Goodbye.

444
00:53:17,969 --> 00:53:19,992
Go right through there,
and down all the steps.

445
00:53:20,204 --> 00:53:21,692
Thank you.

446
00:53:52,926 --> 00:53:56,121
- Well... Small world!
- Yeah.

447
00:53:56,328 --> 00:53:59,625
l almost forgot.
Can you lend me some money?

448
00:53:59,830 --> 00:54:02,127
Oh, yeah.

449
00:54:02,331 --> 00:54:05,423
That's right,
you didn't have any did you?

450
00:54:08,635 --> 00:54:10,863
How much was it you wanted?

451
00:54:11,071 --> 00:54:14,368
l don't know. How much have you got?

452
00:54:14,574 --> 00:54:18,770
Suppose we just split this fifty-fifty.
Here's a thousand lire.

453
00:54:18,976 --> 00:54:22,375
A thousand!
Can you really spare all that?

454
00:54:22,579 --> 00:54:25,978
- lt's about a dollar and a half.
- Oh.

455
00:54:26,181 --> 00:54:32,014
l'll arrange for it to be sent back to you.
What is your address?

456
00:54:32,218 --> 00:54:33,844
Via Margutta 51 .

457
00:54:34,053 --> 00:54:36,576
Via Margutta 51 .

458
00:54:36,789 --> 00:54:38,380
Joe Bradley.

459
00:54:38,922 --> 00:54:41,354
Goodbye. Thank you.

460
00:54:54,800 --> 00:54:58,734
Double my money, eh?
You tell me how?

461
00:54:58,936 --> 00:55:01,563
- Tomorrow.
- Yes, tomorrow.

462
00:57:36,174 --> 00:57:40,835
What a wonderful hair you have.

463
00:57:41,043 --> 00:57:43,475
- Just cut, thank you.
- Just cut?

464
00:57:44,245 --> 00:57:49,077
- Well, then... Cut so?
- Higher.

465
00:57:49,283 --> 00:57:52,478
- Higher? Here?
- More.

466
00:57:54,819 --> 00:57:56,876
- Here!
- Even more.

467
00:57:58,455 --> 00:57:59,751
Where?

468
00:58:01,658 --> 00:58:04,216
- There.
- There.

469
00:58:05,159 --> 00:58:09,616
- Are you sure, Miss?
- l'm quite sure, thank you.

470
00:58:12,664 --> 00:58:15,291
- All off?
- All off.

471
00:58:17,134 --> 00:58:18,430
Off!

472
00:58:27,742 --> 00:58:30,106
- Are you sure?
- Yes!

473
00:58:31,443 --> 00:58:32,739
Yes!

474
00:58:36,114 --> 00:58:37,410
Off!

475
00:58:42,651 --> 00:58:43,947
Off!

476
00:58:49,255 --> 00:58:50,551
Off!

477
00:58:59,963 --> 00:59:03,260
Oh no, no.

478
00:59:04,032 --> 00:59:06,157
Off!

479
00:59:24,946 --> 00:59:28,744
That's a nice camera
you have there. Nice...

480
00:59:30,349 --> 00:59:33,248
You don't mind if l borrow it?

481
00:59:33,918 --> 00:59:35,885
- Miss Webber.
- Just for two minutes.

482
00:59:36,087 --> 00:59:37,678
No.

483
00:59:37,888 --> 00:59:40,878
Go, it's my camera.

484
00:59:49,268 --> 00:59:52,060
You musician, maybe?

485
00:59:52,265 --> 00:59:54,853
You artist, huh?

486
00:59:55,062 --> 00:59:56,685
Painter?

487
00:59:58,592 --> 01:00:01,554
