August!

730
01:27:53,294 --> 01:27:54,923
Thank you.

731
01:27:59,075 --> 01:28:00,543
Bye.

732
01:28:12,978 --> 01:28:14,776
Your Highness.

733
01:28:16,453 --> 01:28:20,258
Dance quietly towards the entrance.
A car is waiting.

734
01:28:20,463 --> 01:28:22,330
- No.
- Your Highness!

735
01:28:22,535 --> 01:28:26,271
You've made a mistake. Let me go!

736
01:28:26,479 --> 01:28:31,763
Will you let me go? Mr Bradley!
Let me go, will you! Mr Bradley!

737
01:29:48,361 --> 01:29:50,669
Hit him again, Smitty!

738
01:29:59,339 --> 01:30:01,713
- Here are my car keys.
- Police!

739
01:30:01,908 --> 01:30:04,081
The other side of the bridge.

740
01:31:14,715 --> 01:31:17,036
- All right?
- Fine, you?

741
01:31:17,246 --> 01:31:19,263
Oh, fine.

742
01:31:24,364 --> 01:31:26,614
You were great back there.

743
01:31:26,827 --> 01:31:29,008
You weren't so bad yourself.

744
01:31:56,117 --> 01:31:57,446
l...

745
01:31:59,026 --> 01:32:02,325
l guess we'd better get out of here.

746
01:32:22,750 --> 01:32:23,646
This is the American Hour,

747
01:32:23,751 --> 01:32:26,971
continuing our programme
of musical selections.

748
01:32:52,728 --> 01:32:57,139
- Everything ruined?
- No. They'll be dry in a minute.

749
01:33:00,371 --> 01:33:03,728
Suits you. You should
always wear my clothes.

750
01:33:05,127 --> 01:33:07,152
Seems l do.

751
01:33:11,534 --> 01:33:14,867
l thought a little wine might be good.

752
01:33:15,774 --> 01:33:18,902
- Shall l cook something?
- No kitchen.

753
01:33:19,110 --> 01:33:22,944
- l always eat out.
- Do you like that?

754
01:33:23,549 --> 01:33:26,279
Well, life isn't always what one likes.

755
01:33:27,321 --> 01:33:32,384
- ls it?
- No, it isn't.

756
01:33:40,470 --> 01:33:42,461
- Tired?
- A little.

757
01:33:42,673 --> 01:33:45,437
- You've had quite a day.
- A wonderful day.

758
01:33:45,644 --> 01:33:50,672
This is the American Hour
with a special news bulletin.

759
01:33:50,883 --> 01:33:54,319
There is no further word
from the bedside of Princess Ann,

760
01:33:54,521 --> 01:33:59,288
who was taken ill yesterday
on the last leg of her European tour.

761
01:33:59,494 --> 01:34:02,258
Rumours suggest
her condition may be serious,

762
01:34:02,464 --> 01:34:06,298
causing alarm and anxiety
among the people in her country.

763
01:34:10,240 --> 01:34:12,299
- The news can wait.
- Yes.

764
01:34:12,509 --> 01:34:15,672
May l have a little more wine?

765
01:34:18,250 --> 01:34:21,549
l'm sorry l couldn't
cook us some dinner.

766
01:34:21,754 --> 01:34:23,847
Did you learn how in school?

767
01:34:24,057 --> 01:34:27,151
l'm a good cook.
l could earn my living at it.

768
01:34:27,361 --> 01:34:30,261
l can sew too, clean a house, iron.

769
01:34:30,465 --> 01:34:32,728
l learned to do all those things,

770
01:34:32,934 --> 01:34:37,268
l just haven't had the chance
to do it for anyone.

771
01:34:40,043 --> 01:34:47,143
Well, looks like l'll have to move
and get a place with a kitchen.

772
01:34:52,192 --> 01:34:53,658
Yes.

773
01:35:18,958 --> 01:35:21,756
l shall have to go now.

774
01:35:37,447 --> 01:35:38,913
Anya...

775
01:35:40,818 --> 01:35:44,686
...there's something l want to tell you.

776
01:35:48,828 --> 01:35:50,887
No, please.

777
01:35:51,498 --> 01:35:53,465
Nothing.

778
01:36:06,650 --> 01:36:09,118
l must go and get dressed.

779
01:36:49,136 --> 01:36:51,536
Stop at the next corner, please.

780
01:36:51,738 --> 01:36:53,034
OK.

781
01:37:10,162 --> 01:37:13,392
- Here?
- Yes.

782
01:37:22,811 --> 01:37:24,836
l have to leave you now.

783
01:37:31,355 --> 01:37:37,089
l'm going to that
corner there and turning.

784
01:37:37,295 --> 01:37:40,458
You stay in the car and drive away.

785
01:37:41,367 --> 01:37:44,359
Promise not to watch me
go beyond the corner.

786
01:37:45,839 --> 01:37:49,002
Just drive away and leave me.

787
01:37:50,711 --> 01:37:52,905
As l leave you.

788
01:37:58,956 --> 01:38:00,582
All right.

789
01:38:03,060 --> 01:38:05,994
l don't know how to say goodbye.

790
01:38:08,733 --> 01:38:11,257
l can't think of any words.

791
01:38:13,606 --> 01:38:16,074
Don't try.

792
01:40:08,114 --> 01:40:10,139
Your Royal Highness,

793
01:40:10,350 --> 01:40:15,288
twenty-four hours,
they can't all be blank.

794
01:40:17,358 --> 01:40:19,154
They are not.

795
01:40:20,196 --> 01:40:23,426
What explanation am l
to offer Their Majesties?

796
01:40:23,632 --> 01:40:26,931
l was indisposed. l am better.

797
01:40:29,607 --> 01:40:34,374
Ma'am, you must appreciate
that l have my duty to perform,

798
01:40:34,580 --> 01:40:37,743
just as Your Royal
Highness has her duty.

799
01:40:37,951 --> 01:40:39,383
Your Excellency,

800
01:40:39,587 --> 01:40:44,115
l trust you will not find it necessary
to use that word again.

801
01:40:44,325 --> 01:40:49,695
Were l not completely aware of
my duty to my family and my country,

802
01:40:49,899 --> 01:40:53,027
l would not have come back tonight.

803
01:40:58,309 --> 01:41:00,606
Or indeed, ever again.

804
01:41:07,988 --> 01:41:15,020
And now, since l understand
we have a very full schedule today,

805
01:41:15,230 --> 01:41:18,529
you have my permission to withdraw.

806
01:41:34,287 --> 01:41:37,654
No milk and crackers.

807
01:41:43,898 --> 01:41:47,561
That will be all thank you, Countess.

808
01:42:47,844 --> 01:42:50,972
- Did you really get it?
- What?

809
01:42:51,181 --> 01:42:54,081
The princess exclusive.
Did you get it?

810
01:42:54,284 --> 01:42:57,253
- No, l didn't.
- What? That's impossible.

811
01:42:57,456 --> 01:42:59,947
- Coffee?
- Don't hold out on me.

812
01:43:00,159 --> 01:43:03,492
- Who's holding out?
- You are. l know too much.

813
01:43:03,697 --> 01:43:08,191
First you ask about an exclusive
on the princess, next you disappear.

814
01:43:08,403 --> 01:43:12,931
Then l hear a rumour from the
embassy that she's out on the town.

815
01:43:13,142 --> 01:43:16,600
Do you believe every rumour
that comes your way?

816
01:43:16,813 --> 01:43:21,580
There's a lot of other rumours.
About a shindig down by the river,

817
01:43:21,786 --> 01:43:25,745
and the arrest of eight secret
service men from a certain country.

818
01:43:25,957 --> 01:43:30,860
Then she makes
a miraculous recovery. lt all adds up.

819
01:43:31,064 --> 01:43:37,368
Don't think you'll raise the price,
a deal's a deal. Now come on.

820
01:43:37,572 --> 01:43:41,440
- Where is that story?
- l have no story.

821
01:43:43,779 --> 01:43:47,840
- Now what was the idea...
- Joe.

822
01:43:48,051 --> 01:43:50,485
- Wait till you see these.
- lrving.

823
01:43:50,687 --> 01:43:52,654
Hi, Mr Hennessy.

824
01:43:52,857 --> 01:43:54,222
lrving!

825
01:43:56,528 --> 01:44:00,362
- What's the idea?
- You charge in, spilling things!

826
01:44:00,567 --> 01:44:03,229
- Me?
- l warned you before.

827
01:44:03,436 --> 01:44:06,428
- Remember?
- Look at my pants.

828
01:44:06,640 --> 01:44:10,303
- Come and dry them off.
- Nuts to that.

829
01:44:10,512 --> 01:44:13,276
- Did you tell him about Smitty?
- Who?

830
01:44:13,483 --> 01:44:16,042
- Wait till you...
- lrving!

831
01:44:16,252 --> 01:44:18,652
There you go again, lrving.

832
01:44:21,126 --> 01:44:24,356
- Joe...
- Save that till later.

833
01:44:24,562 --> 01:44:29,090
- Why don't you go home and shave?
- Shave?

834
01:44:29,302 --> 01:44:32,863
Or else keep quiet
till we're finished talking.

835
01:44:33,073 --> 01:44:35,473
What kind of routine is that?

836
01:44:35,676 --> 01:44:37,643
What are you up to? Who's Smitty?

837
01:44:37,846 --> 01:44:41,043
- A guy we met.
- What is there to look at?

838
01:44:41,250 --> 01:44:45,016
Just some of lrving's dames.
You wouldn't like them.

839
01:44:45,221 --> 01:44:48,485
- Maybe you would.
- Don't change the subject.

840
01:44:48,692 --> 01:44:51,889
- Yesterday you said...
- l had a good lead.

841
01:44:52,097 --> 01:44:57,899
But l was wrong, that's all
there is to it. There is no story.

842
01:44:59,338 --> 01:45:00,634
OK.

843
01:45:00,841 --> 01:45:06,803
She's holding the press interview
today. Maybe you can get that story.

844
01:45:08,717 --> 01:45:10,480
And you owe me $500.

845
01:45:10,687 --> 01:45:15,488
- Take it from my salary, $50 a week.
- Don't think l won't.

846
01:45:17,827 --> 01:45:20,955
What gives?
Have we had a better offer?

847
01:45:21,165 --> 01:45:22,791
lrving...

848
01:45:23,302 --> 01:45:26,863
l don't know just how
to tell you this, but...

849
01:45:27,073 --> 01:45:29,267
Wait till l sit down.

850
01:45:31,078 --> 01:45:37,540
Well, in regard to the story
that goes with these,

851
01:45:37,753 --> 01:45:40,244
there is no story.

852
01:45:41,524 --> 01:45:44,254
Why not?

853
01:45:44,461 --> 01:45:47,555
l mean, not as far as l'm concerned.

854
01:45:59,212 --> 01:46:05,014
The pictures came out pretty well.
Want to have a look at them?

855
01:46:15,099 --> 01:46:18,796
How about a blow-up
from a negative that size?

856
01:46:20,773 --> 01:46:22,900
- Her first cigarette!
- Yeah.

857
01:46:23,509 --> 01:46:25,305
The Mouth of Truth.

858
01:46:27,514 --> 01:46:32,144
l had a caption in mind:
''Barber cuts in.''

859
01:46:33,154 --> 01:46:36,020
Here's the key shot
for the whole layout.

860
01:46:36,725 --> 01:46:38,750
''The Wall Where
Wishes Come True.''

861
01:46:38,962 --> 01:46:40,428
Joe, that's good.

862
01:46:40,630 --> 01:46:44,464
Lead off with that,
then follow up with the wishes?

863
01:46:44,669 --> 01:46:48,571
l got that from the file.
''Princess lnspects Police.''

864
01:46:48,774 --> 01:46:50,503
Yeah...

865
01:46:50,710 --> 01:46:53,873
''Police lnspects Princess.''

866
01:46:54,080 --> 01:46:56,071
- How about that?
- Pretty good.

867
01:46:56,283 --> 01:46:57,909
l got a topper for you.

868
01:47:00,487 --> 01:47:02,113
- Wow!
- ls that a shot?

869
01:47:02,324 --> 01:47:05,020
- What a picture!
- ls that a shot?

870
01:47:05,227 --> 01:47:07,354
''Bodyguard Gets Body Blow.''

871
01:47:07,563 --> 01:47:10,930
No, how about this?
''Crowned Head?'' Huh?

872
01:47:11,134 --> 01:47:14,433
Oh, l get it. Joe, you got...

873
01:47:20,647 --> 01:47:22,841
She's fair game, Joe.

874
01:47:23,049 --> 01:47:25,745
lt's always open season
on princesses.

875
01:47:28,089 --> 01:47:32,389
- You must be out of your mind.
- l know, but...

876
01:47:32,594 --> 01:47:37,497
Look, l can't prevent you from
selling the pictures, if you want to.

877
01:47:37,700 --> 01:47:41,431
- You'll get a good price for them.
- Yeah.

878
01:47:47,380 --> 01:47:50,907
- Are you going to the interview?
- Are you?

879
01:47:51,117 --> 01:47:53,608
Yeah. lt's an assignment, isn't it?

880
01:47:54,555 --> 01:47:56,181
Yeah.

881
01:48:00,796 --> 01:48:02,319
l'll see you.

882
01:48:17,482 --> 01:48:20,974
lt ain't much, but it's home.

883
01:48:30,598 --> 01:48:33,999
Ladies and gentlemen,
please approach.

884
01:49:02,805 --> 01:49:04,772
Her Royal Highness.

885
01:49:33,643 --> 01:49:35,473
Your Royal Highness,

886
01:49:35,679 --> 01:49:38,147
the ladies and gentlemen
of the press.

887
01:50:15,061 --> 01:50:16,357
Ladies and gentlemen,

888
01:50:16,563 --> 01:50:19,555
Her Royal Highness
will now answer your questions.

889
01:50:19,767 --> 01:50:21,826
l believe at the outset,
Your Highness,

890
01:50:22,036 --> 01:50:25,699
that l should express
the pleasure of all of us,

891
01:50:25,908 --> 01:50:29,435
at your recovery
from the recent illness.

892
01:50:31,113 --> 01:50:32,478
Thank you.

893
01:50:33,584 --> 01:50:35,210
Does Your Highness believe

894
01:50:35,420 --> 01:50:40,551
that federation could be a solution
to Europe's economic problems?

895
01:50:42,194 --> 01:50:44,628
l am in favour of any measure

896
01:50:44,831 --> 01:50:48,824
which would lead
to closer cooperation in Europe.

897
01:50:49,937 --> 01:50:52,667
And what, in the opinion
of Your Highness,

898
01:50:52,874 --> 01:50:56,537
is the outlook for
friendship among nations?

899
01:50:57,446 --> 01:51:00,073
l have every faith in it...

900
01:51:01,951 --> 01:51:05,648
...as l have faith
in relations between people.

901
01:51:11,364 --> 01:51:15,824
May l say, speaking for
my own press service...

902
01:51:17,070 --> 01:51:21,939
...we believe that Your Highness's
faith will not be unjustified.

903
01:51:25,214 --> 01:51:28,808
l am so glad to hear you say it.

904
01:51:30,920 --> 01:51:34,913
Which of the cities visited
did Your Highness enjoy the most?

905
01:51:49,043 --> 01:51:53,912
Each in its own way
was unforgettable.

906
01:51:54,116 --> 01:51:56,413
lt would be difficult to...

907
01:51:58,755 --> 01:52:04,058
Rome! By all means, Rome.

908
01:52:06,632 --> 01:52:13,038
l will cherish my visit here
in memory, as long as l live.

909
01:52:19,715 --> 01:52:22,684
Despite your indisposition,
Your Highness?

910
01:52:25,021 --> 01:52:26,647
Despite that.

911
01:52:27,758 --> 01:52:30,282
Photographs may now be taken.

912
01:52:58,896 --> 01:53:01,125
Thank you, ladies and gentlemen.

913
01:53:01,332 --> 01:53:03,732
Thank you very much.

914
01:53:03,935 --> 01:53:09,238
l would now like to meet some of
the ladies and gentlemen of the press.

915
01:53:24,661 --> 01:53:27,561
Hitchcock, ''Chicago Daily News''.

916
01:53:27,764 --> 01:53:31,723
- l'm so happy to see you here.
- Thank you.

917
01:53:31,936 --> 01:53:34,734
Scanziani, ''La Suisse''.

918
01:53:37,342 --> 01:53:39,810
Klinger, Deutsche Presse Agentur.

919
01:53:43,117 --> 01:53:45,915
Maurice Montabré, ''Le Figaro''.

920
01:53:51,861 --> 01:53:54,887
Sytske Galema,
''De Linie'', Amsterdam.

921
01:53:58,402 --> 01:54:00,768
Jacques Ferrier, ''lci Paris''.

922
01:54:04,510 --> 01:54:07,536
Gross, ''Davar Tel Aviv''.

923
01:54:10,584 --> 01:54:13,484
Cortes Cavanillas, ''ABC Madrid''.

924
01:54:17,459 --> 01:54:19,358
Lampe, ''New York Herald Tribune''.

925
01:54:19,562 --> 01:54:22,656
- Good afternoon.
- Good afternoon.

926
01:54:22,866 --> 01:54:26,393
lrving Radovich, CR Photo Service.

927
01:54:26,604 --> 01:54:29,573
How do you do?

928
01:54:29,774 --> 01:54:31,570
May l present Your Highness

929
01:54:31,776 --> 01:54:34,802
with some commemorative photos
of your visit to Rome?

930
01:54:40,854 --> 01:54:43,720
Thank you so very much.

931
01:54:52,135 --> 01:54:56,070
Joe Bradley, American News Service.

932
01:54:56,774 --> 01:54:59,674
So happy, Mr Bradley.

933
01:55:03,316 --> 01:55:06,376
Moriones, ''La Vanguardia'', Barcelona.

934
01:55:09,790 --> 01:55:12,850
Stephen House, of the
''London Exchange Telegraph''.

935
01:55:13,061 --> 01:55:14,756
Good afternoon.

936
01:55:16,399 --> 01:55:19,265
De Aldisio, Agence Press.

